<h2>Editorial Offices</h2>

<p>
The Editorial Board operates through several offices responsible for
maintaining narrative stability and archival continuity across the
Journal’s published memoranda.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Directorate of Narrative Stability</strong><br/>
Monitors consistency across published historical interpretations.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Bureau of Historical Realignment</strong><br/>
Coordinates minor adjustments when previously settled conclusions
require contextual clarification.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Office of Archival Continuity</strong><br/>
Maintains cross-references between memoranda and related materials,
including documents whose circulation history is incomplete.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Satire Singularity Monitoring Unit</strong><br/>
Conducts ongoing analysis of conditions under which real-world developments
begin to resemble satirical commentary.
</p>

<p>
The Unit evaluates whether institutional statements, policy decisions,
and geopolitical events remain sufficiently distinguishable from parody
to preserve interpretive clarity within the archive.
</p>

<p>Indicators monitored include:</p>

<ul>
<li>public confusion between satire and official announcements</li>
<li>policy statements structurally indistinguishable from comedic premises</li>
<li>situations in which satire requires minimal exaggeration to remain plausible</li>
<li>instances in which satirical publications are cited as policy analysis</li>
</ul>

<p>
When necessary, the Unit may issue <em>Absurdity Threshold Advisories</em>
recommending temporary reductions in institutional irony.
</p>

<p>
Current assessment: <strong>Satire Singularity Risk Level — Elevated but manageable.</strong>
</p>

